Protocol is a set of rules and guidelines that enables communications between two or more networks. The authentication protocol of Sunbird provides: 

1. A secure API endpoint to register new organisations

2. A secure API endpoint to register new users

3. A secure API endpoint to register users to organizations

4. A secure API endpoint to de-register users from organizations

5. A secure API endpoint to update user details

6. A secure API endpoint to update organisation details

7. A secure API endpoint to auto-login a user into SUnbird (Single-Sign-On)
